posts.title: Michigan early voting started today, I was first in line, first to vote, but the machine rejected my
posts.content:
Ballot twenty+ times. Wife tried, and it wouldn't take hers either.

I didn't trust the "Provisional" slot, because they said there is no way to ever know if the ballot was actually run through.

The ended up resending the ballot data, twice, but that didn't work.

Then they powered down and rebooted the machine, but that didn't work.

Then they shut it down, cut the seal, and pulled the memory card and backup memory card and verified they were "EV" cards (early voting has a different block of ballot numbers than Election day--good to know).

Before reinserting the cards, I said "blow on them first" and got a good laugh from the crowd now forming behind us.

They got the machine rebooted and still no-go.

The last attempt before I was going to spoil my ballot and come back tomorrow, I noticed the tear off strip at the top of the ballot was getting flimsy and about to fall off due to all the insertions.

It was that moment I looked at the gal and saw in her eyes she knew what was wrong too.

They forgot to tear off the strip that matches the ballot at the top, so the machine kept saying the ballot was invalid.

They put out the basket for the tear off's and I helped set up the table they forgot about, and we all had a good laugh.

It was interesting to see how professional they were in following their procedures and validating each step of the process, even the machine seal process has to be verified and validated.

Michigan may not be lost yet.
